The paper deals with the computation of betweenness centrality, which is a measure of node importance in a network. This topic is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including social network analysis (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), streaming and dynamic algorithms (cs.SD), network science (cs.NI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Given that the paper proposes new algorithms for fully-dynamic networks, cs.SD is a strong candidate. However, since the paper also discusses upper bounds on graph diameter and the performance of the algorithms in large-scale experiments, cs.DS and cs.SI are also likely categories. Finally, since the paper proposes algorithms with provable guarantees, cs.NI and cs.LG are also possible categories.
